### Test ValidateAccessToken Endpoint
### This file tests the token validation functionality
### 
### BEST PRACTICE: Use Authorization header for JWT tokens (Steps 3-6)
### BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY: Request body still supported (Steps 7-8)

### Step 1: First get a fresh token by signing in
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/customer-authenticate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "vlad.crishan20@gmail.com"
}

###

### Step 2: Verify OTP to get a fresh access token
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "vlad.crishan20@gmail.com",
  "code": "REPLACE_WITH_OTP_FROM_EMAIL"
}

### Copy the accessToken from the response above and use it in the test below

###

### Step 3: Test ValidateAccessToken with Authorization header (RECOMMENDED)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..EQUI1Zm_SEpJvim12RZgaQ0z75QmlGyCkC0itKIUFBQ
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 4: Test ValidateAccessToken with Authorization header (no Bearer prefix)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Authorization: REPLACE_WITH_FRESH_ACCESS_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 5: Test ValidateAccessToken with invalid token in Authorization header
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 6: Test ValidateAccessToken with missing token (should fail)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 7: Test ValidateAccessToken with request body (backward compatibility)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "REPLACE_WITH_FRESH_ACCESS_TOKEN"
}

###

### Step 8: Test ValidateAccessToken with Bearer prefix in request body (backward compatibility)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "Bearer REPLACE_WITH_FRESH_ACCESS_TOKEN"
}

###

### Expected Response for valid tokens:
### {
###   "isValid": true,
###   "expiresAt": "/Date(1760194266000-0000)/",
###   "customerId": "57f0deab-61df-4172-a474-1bcdc07cb846",
###   "email": "vlad.crishan20@gmail.com"
### }
